text: Wow people as always make a big mess from everything. If in this world is something that I distaste with all of my being that is arrogance among ignorance! We don't know shit about this Earth, nor even about our own body, and yet we think we know everything about the Universe or about existence in general! How ignorant and arrogant in the same time! The universe is incommensurable and we are sooo small, still we think we know how things were made.  Some of you are bashing on the others beliefs with no shame! Let's be clear out there, you say that the existence of God is unproven and "God" was created by humans in order to enslave the people physiologically and on a mental level. That the books aren't any proofs because these were created by ''the hand of human''. *But*... guess what? The scientists are human too! And the theories are human made too and most likely this'll be proven wrong again and again. Theories are just assumptions based on researches. God (in some chases) is just an assumption based on experiences of human beings trough their life. So who are you to say to the others in who or what they must believe?  If someone believe in facts then.. *it's ok*, if someone believe in what they feel then.. *it's ok* again. We don't have the right to step on what someone feels/knows/likes/dislikes/believes/approves/disapproves and so on. If someone don't force you to live in their terms then you don't force anyone else! Is that simple.  Personal I believe in one God, bigger/greater than how any religion describes Him. I feel It, I see It, I sense It, I smell It, I breath It, I touch It, I eat It every flipping day! And I don't pretend that this is ''the biggest truth'' that everyone must accept it, no! This is my truth... You have yours! Everything is perception. If you want to perceive this world as something made from matter and nothing more, fine. If you don't see the life flying all over the place, it's ok, I won't judge you. Personal I don't believe that we come out of nothing, that everything was a random effect. The cells, the atoms, the Universe, *us*, everything was so perfect programed at the finest. So, if some people finds "God'' bs, I find ''the theory of nothing'' bs and hardly to believe. :)  But in the end I have the courage to doubt myself, what about you? :)
